  "commentary": "With SPX at 6588.17 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma walls (6580-6590 holding -26.5M and -25.5M respectively), dealers are being forced to buy this dip aggressively as their short gamma positions hemorrhage delta. The breakout regime combined with the 467% GEX surge indicates we're seeing violent dealer flow amplification, and with spot sandwiched between the max negative gamma at 6580 and positive gamma resistance at 6605, expect continued whipsaw action until we clear above 6605 or break below the 6575-6580 support cluster.\n\nKey inflection point is 6605 - if we push through, dealers flip to selling mode and momentum could accelerate higher, but failure here likely sends us back toward the 6575-6580 negative gamma magnet where dealer buying should provide support.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6575 and 6605 until one side breaks decisively.",
